ASUS has revealed its new ROG Zephyrus M gaming laptop, which boasts an 8th-gen Intel Core processor and Nvidia GeForce 10-series graphics card. The device is equipped with either an Nvidia GeForce GTX 1070 or GTX 1060 card, and boasts a 144Hz full HD G-Sync display. A hinge at the back of the laptop raises its chassis when the lid is lifted, allowing for improved airflow through its 20mm-thick body. The ROG Zephyrus M is available for preorder internationally and is priced at $2,199 and $,1899 for the GTX 1070 and GTX 1060 models respectively. Both models are fitted with an Intel Core i7 8th-gen hexa-core processor.